
ZCOLORS
+++++++

SUMMARY
-------
Controls the color display of contour lines.

SYNTAX
------

  ``ZCOLORS  {ON|OFF}  {options}``
   where options is currently limited to:


  ``LIST c1 c2 ... cn``


  ``More options will be added in the future.``

INPUT
-----
   :ON:  Turn color display of contour lines on.
    
   :OFF:  Turn color display of contour lines off.
    
   :LIST c1 c2 . cn:  Set the list of contour color names to use.  Each
       entry in this list is used for the corresponding contour level.  If
       the number of contour levels is larger than the length of this list,
       the entire list is repeated.
    
   :cn:  The name of a color from SAC's current color table.
    
DEFAULT VALUES
--------------

  ``ZCOLORS OFF LIST RED GREEN BLUE``

SEE COMMANDS
------------
   CONTOUR_, COLOR_

LATEST REVISION
---------------
   April 30, 1990 (Version 10.5b)

